Jetro to Sell Alcohol to U.S. Restaurants, Independent Says

-- B y   M i k e   C o h e n
-- 
2011-12-11T10:40:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-11/jetro-to-sell-alcohol-to-u-s-restaurants-independent-says.html
JRD Holdings Inc. plans to begin
selling alcohol to restaurants and stores in the  United States ,
the  Sunday Independent  reported, citing Nathan Kirsh, the South
African billionaire with a controlling state in the company.  The food and beverage distributor, which operates under the
name Jetro and has annual revenue of $7 billion, will need to
secure about 250,000 cases of wine a week to supply its 400,000
clients, Kirsh said, according to the Johannesburg-based
newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mike Cohen in  Cape Town  at 
 mcohen21@bloomberg.net ;  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net . 